# {{.Name}}'s coaching workspace

This directory is a [`fit-agent`](https://github.com/jogvan-k/fit-agent)
workspace synced with [intervals.icu](https://intervals.icu). It is
designed to be opened as an [OpenClaw](https://docs.openclaw.ai)
workspace so the coaching skills under `skills/` are loaded
automatically.

## What is here

| Path | Owner | Purpose |
|------|-------|---------|
| `ATHLETE-PROFILE.md` | you & the agent | who you are, your goals, constraints |
| `TRAINING-PLAN.md` | the agent (created on demand) | the current macro plan |
| `skills/**/SKILL.md` | the agent | coaching workflows for the agent |
| `fit-agent/wellness/*.yaml` | machine | daily wellness, regenerated by `fit-agent fetch` |
| `fit-agent/activities/*.yaml` | machine | per-activity summaries, regenerated by `fit-agent fetch` |
| `fit-agent/planned-workouts/*.md` | shared | next workouts; `fit-agent push-workouts` syncs them to intervals.icu |
| `fit-agent/.cache/**` | machine | raw intervals.icu JSON + FIT files (source of truth) |

Files marked **machine** are regenerated on every `fit-agent fetch` —
do not hand-edit them, your changes will be lost. Files marked **agent**
are never overwritten by the CLI.

## Common commands

```sh
fit-agent fetch --since 30d        # pull recent activities + wellness from intervals.icu
fit-agent push-workouts --dry-run  # preview what would be pushed back
fit-agent push-workouts            # push planned-workouts/*.md to intervals.icu
```

The CLI is a tool the AI agent invokes; it does not call any LLM
itself. Coaching prompts live in `skills/`.

## How the coaching pipeline fits together

```
training-plan-coach  →  TRAINING-PLAN.md  →  workout-builder  →  planned-workouts/*.md
                                                                  ↑
                                              training-session-coach (daily adjustments)
```

`TRAINING-PLAN.md` is created the first time the agent runs the
training-plan-coach skill. It does not exist out of the box.
